07838nam a22010935i 9783110672268DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106722687 a10.1515/97831106722682doi  a(DE-B1597)534969  a(OCoLC)1158141625  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a49000aMaltese Linguistics on the Danube /ced. by Slavomír Čéplö, Jaroslav Drobný. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (VIII, 322 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudia Typologica [STTYP] : Beihefte / Supplements STUF - Sprachtypologie und Universalienforschung / Language Typology and Universals ,x1617-2957 ;v2400tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tPart I: Historical Linguistics -- tMaltese and North African linguistics: Common roots and areal divergence -- tThe diachrony of word-final obstruent devoicing in Maltese -- tThe history of the Maltese short vowels -- tAn observation on the ḥāl construction in Maltese -- tMinsel. An etymological database for lexemes of Arabic origin in Maltese -- tPart II: Syntax -- tWill it agree or not? Syntactic overgeneralization leading to agreement mismatches in Maltese -- tArgument extension in Maltese -- tLanqas, negative concord and predicate negation in Maltese -- tFrom variation towards the grammar of Maltese prepositions – first steps -- tForm and behavior of Maltese prepositions – A usage-based approach -- tPart III: Phonology -- tTo be or not to be an affricate – affricated stops in Maltese -- tRevisiting the definite article in Maltese -- tIndex of Authors -- tIndex of Languages -- tIndex of Subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume brings together a dozen papers on various aspects of Maltese, relevant also for the study of related languages and general descriptive and typological linguistics.The diachronic section begins with an analysis of the place of Maltese in its North African context (Souag). Avram and van Putten then provide analyses of the development of Maltese phonological inventory, the former discussing obstruent devoicing, the latter tracing the evolution of Maltese short vowels. Sumikazu examines a type of circumstantial clause in Maltese and the section concludes with a description of a digital etymological lexicon of Maltese (Gatt).Turning to syntax, Borg and Amaira analyze agreement mismatch in a number of syntactic constructions, Fabri discusses argument extension and Čéplö and Lucas examine the role of the focus particle lanqas in Maltese negation. Stolz and Levkovych provide a thorough analysis of the syntax and semantics of Maltese prepositions, while Schmidt, Vorholt and Witt offer a quantitative study of their distribution and use.Closing out the volume, Alexander examines in detail the phonetics of Maltese affricated stops, while Ellul and Galea analyze the epenthetic vowel alternation in the Maltese definite article.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aHistorical Linguistics.  aMaltese.  aPhonology.  aSyntax.1 aAmaira, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvram, Andrei A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzzopardi-Alexander, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorg, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrobný, Jaroslav, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEllul, Leanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFabri, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab